    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1913-02-18T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1913-02-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="489"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d489">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 839.51/957.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Minister</gloss> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>. <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Santo Domingo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-02-18">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 18, 1913</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The Government is in desperate straits unless some kind of loan is immediately
                    consummated. The President has been compelled of pay out large sums for the
                    expenses of the late war; these were proper expenses and the sums used to pay
                    them were advanced by Michelena, to be charged to the loan. But owing to the
                    uncertainty about the conclusion of the loan, Michelena absolutely refuses to
                    advance another dollar.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Russell</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
